    <p>• Span­ish news­pa­per ABC yes­ter­day is­sued an apol­ogy to Ansu Fati after its match re­port of Barcelona’s 5-1 Cham­pi­ons League win over</p>
    <p>Ferenc­varos on Tues­day com­pared his pace to that of a “black street ven­dor flee­ing the po­lice”.</p>
    <p>The 17-year-old Guinea Bis­sau-born Spain for­ward scored the sec­ond goal for the hosts, but con­tro­versy erupted af­ter­wards, with team­mate An­toine Griez­mann and pun­dit Gary Lineker tak­ing ex­cep­tion to the re­port that had racial un­der­tones.</p>
    <p>ABC is known to be a right-lean­ing pub­li­ca­tion but de­spite its apol­ogy, Barca are re­port­edly set to take le­gal ac­tion over the mat­ter.</p>


